description: @nike marks its first collaboration with @elissa_steamer’s @gnarhunters with a new iteration of the Nike SB Zoom Blazer Mid. A black tumbled leather upper and contrasting heel and sole are put together for a monochromatic color scheme, while the skate and surf label’s diamond-shaped “G” logo is printed all over a muted charcoal swoosh. The sneaker will be available for purchase on June 29 at Nike’s web store.Photo: Nike

@nike continues its re-release of vintage trainers from 1998, this time with a black, grey and white colorway of the Air Ghost Racer. It is crafted with a number of panels in leather and nylon mesh, all matched with metallic TPU overlays. Cop a pair over at @43einhalb’s web store for approximately $136 USD.Photo: 43einhalb

Taking on the Match silhouette, @patta_nl and @mephistousa have returned for another capsule of handmade shoes. Coming in either black or white, the labels have added a selection of subtle design touches to the athletic-inspired silhouette. Cop a pair at Patta’s Milan, Amsterdam or London location, or from their web store on June 28.Photo: @walidlabri/@violette_esmeralda

@adidasoriginals fuses retro ‘90 elements with modern footwear technology by releasing a “Solar Green/Core Black” colorway of the Ozweego. Cop a pair over at adidas’ web store for $115 USD on June 30.Photo: @adidas

Take a look at @dior’s new sneaker silhouettes that debuted at its Spring/Summer 2020 runway presentation. Alongside the now-iconic B23 shoes, Dior introduced translucent boots and running shoes inspired by the uniform of seasonal artist collaborator @danielarsham. Swipe to see what the collection has to offer.Photo: PA Mulier/@hypebeastfr

@nike has dropped a “Cold Gray”/”Peak White”/Light Grey/Black iteration of the Blazer.  Executed in soft suede, off-white panels at the forefoot and toe contrast the moody swathe of grey and black across much of the upper. Cop a pair over at Nike’s Chinese site for approximately $115 USD.Photos: Nike

Here’s a first look at EE x @theofficialai3 ‘Answer V’ sneaker. Known for his impact on the world of shorts within the industry, sportswear designer @ericemanuel has proved his aesthetic on and for sneakers is nothing to be taken lightly. What are your thoughts on these re-imagined retros’?Photos: Eddie Lee / HYPEBEAST

@reebok and @baitme come together to release the latest iteration of the Instapump Fury model, clad in the colors of several @toystory characters. The sneakers come in mismatching colors for each foot. The left side is dressed in palettes of purple and green, referencing tones of Buzz Lightyear. The right foot Complete with black and white cow-patterns at the side panel, light blue denim underlays are placed next to hits of yellow, a reference to Sheriff Woody. The sneaker will see a limited release in celebration for the screening of the upcoming Toy Story 4.Photos: BAIT

@openingceremony and @vans have unveiled their latest footwear collaboration, this time around dressing the Old Skool sneaker in a lux satin shell. The shoe will be available in three vibrant colorways in line with the summer season, and will be available for purchase on June 21st for $100 at Opening Ceremony‘s retail and online stores.Photo: @bye.loveleo

description: @crocs has teamed up with @barneysny for two punk-inspired makeovers. This Air Tailwind ‘79 from the “Hawkins High School” half of the collaboration is one of the highlights of the set, featuring the fictional school’s team colors on the vintage running shoe with logo patches on the heels and Stranger Things branding on the tongue.
